│ I added a targeted fix in InstCombine's simplifyIRemMulShl to handle the      │
│ problematic signed-remainder pattern directly and avoid the incorrect rewrite │
│ to negation.                                                                  │
│                                                                               │
│ Summary of the change:                                                        │
│ - Detect the specific srem case: numerator is shl nsw X, C, and denominator   │
│ is mul nsw X, (2^C - 1). This corresponds to Y being a power of 2 and Z + 1   │
│ == Y in the matcher.                                                          │
│ - For that pattern, replace the remainder with X. This is the mathematically  │
│ correct result for signed remainder: X*2^C = X*(2^C-1) + X, so the remainder  │
│ is X for all X.                                                               │
│ - The replacement occurs early in simplifyIRemMulShl, before any general      │
│ transforms, ensuring we do not fall through to the buggy rewrite to -X.       │
│                                                                               │
│ This avoids the miscompile shown by the reproducer where instcombine          │
│ incorrectly produces sub nsw 0, %X (i.e., -X) instead of yielding X.          │
│                                                                               │
│ If you want me to iterate further (some tests expect additional               │
│ canonicalizations), I can refine the guards or placement.                     │
